    verification scaffoldCommitGateRetroGate : Test { :>> id = "63940516-2c7d-4e8f-c139-51627384c00e"; :>> title = "Sprint 139 retro gate (autonomous, D0049)"; :>> createdAt = "2026-06-23"; :>> createdBy = "claudeOpus"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::analyze; :>> procedureText = "Autonomous retro (D0049). WELL: LIVE-testing the scaffolded gate (real git init + a bad .sysml -> aborted commit) proved the downstream gate works end to end with zero conda — far stronger than asserting hook contents. AVOIDABLE-ISSUE SCAN: one avoidable self-inflicted nit (D0047 class) caught + fixed — the kernel-free assertion is a crude substring check, and the hook's own comment 'no kernel/conda' tripped it; reworded to 'no JVM kernel'; LESSON: a negative substring assertion must not be tripped by the artifact's own prose. NON-blocking forward note (NOT debt): a downstream CI template is deferred (it needs the released keel binary, which is the releaseWorkflow task). Estimate 2 pts held. 6 deployment tasks remain (cargoReleaseMetadata next)."; }
    part scaffoldCommitGateRetroGateR1 : TestResult { :>> id = "63940516-2c7d-4e8f-c139-51627384c00f"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "184bbfc"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-06-23"; :>> judgedBy = "claudeOpus"; }
